    <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0;"><strong>Ecosystem friction isn&#8217;t categorised.</strong> When a founder travels to raise capital, they are thrown into the exact same administrative bucket and backlog as a family going to Disney World. The issuance of pure B-1 (Business) visas is virtually non-existent (falling from an already low 490 in FY22 to just 470 in FY24). For the African tech ecosystem, this means &#8220;business travel&#8221; isn&#8217;t treated with any dedicated urgency by US immigration systems; it is merely an subset of general visitor processing.</p>
